==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hemitropous
<hw>He*mit"ro*pous</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Hemitrope</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Turned half round; half inverted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the raphe terminating about
half way between the chalaza and the orifice; amphitropous; -- said of
an ovule.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemitrope</ent>⟦br⟧
